    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName>
                <date>March 2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> 1833</date>
            </p>
            <p>My Dear Friend,</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">This day your letter per <persName>Mr<lb/> Hart</persName> was
                handed me by <persName>Mr Moses</persName>, <persName>Mr Hart</persName> not<lb/>
                being a visitor of ours) I am <add>not</add> intending to<lb/> apologize for my long
                silence for as you say<lb/> (altho' I find sufficient to occupy me during<lb/> the
                day.) I could find a few minutes of an<lb/> evening after my <sic>lettle</sic> ones
                go to bed to<lb/> write but in truth, I feel no desire to write<lb/> any one any
                more, I have not any thing pleasing<lb/> to communicate nothing by <sic>whic</sic> I
                can interest<lb/> and why should I impose the task on any friends<lb/> to
                    <sic>prase</sic> my dull epistles I am glad to hear of<lb/> the well doing of
                them all and, if I could<lb/> communicate pleasant circumstances I would with<lb/>
                pleasure, shall I recapitulate the story of<lb/> no servants, the dislike of the
                want of Judaism<lb/> reigning here—My fear of the im<add>?</add>sions of<lb/> my
                children should I have to raise them here my<lb/> discontent at being far away from
                my dear Mother<lb/> family &amp; old friends, no I think it wiser, to<lb/> bear all
                the evils in silence <add>which</add> also beset <add>us</add> in our<lb/> passage
                through this life of trial, and let<lb/> others whose fate is brighter enjoy
                it—<lb/> My sweet children are thank God well and<lb/> improving in beauty and
                intelligence I<lb/>
                <persName>Rosalie</persName> as <add>?</add> she is beginning to learn,<lb/> and
                    <persName>Rehine</persName> can say his prayers alone I shall<lb/> try to give
                them a correct idea of our religion,<lb/> my babe <persName>Sarah</persName> is a
                very handsome child the<lb/> handsomest of mine, black eyes and good skin.</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p><persName>Sarah</persName> is not married yet nor is there any<lb/> prospect at
                present times to dull with her<lb/> beau- her mother has by this time repented<lb/>
                having given up her boarders, for <persName>Master<lb/> Hillel</persName> has
                cheated her in their store<lb/> business and gone off <persName>Sam</persName> is
                another<lb/> Rascal, and <persName>Hyman</persName> on the track poor weak<lb/>
                woman to let those children treat her so<lb/> and to let one follow the steps of the
                rest<lb/> I pity her)<sic>blindess</sic>, the girls cannot get the<lb/> opportunity
                to be worse but are very much<lb/> neglected <persName>Abby</persName> is very wild
                I wish she was<lb/> safely housed— I wish you Joy on the arrival<lb/> of your
                Brother I hope it will be a satisfaction,<lb/> is your sister Married? give my love
                to <persName>Sarah<lb/> Lyon</persName> &amp; <persName>A Allen</persName>, and all
                friends—do mention<lb/> whether <persName>Elkalah's</persName> child was the only
                one the<lb/> or what more particular—we were very<lb/> surprised at <persName>Mr
                    Hart's</persName> return without a wife,<lb/> his Brother celebrated his wedding
                day I am<lb/> told do you know the reason? You have no<lb/> apology for your short
                letters be more<lb/> particular and write plainer I cannot read all<lb/> you words
                    <persName>Mr Bloch</persName> says as you did not mention<lb/> him he
                    <add>shall</add> not you, so you see he is particular—<lb/>
                <persName>Eleanor</persName> is still living with <persName>Mrs
                Moses</persName><lb/> who is not at all particular, but she<lb/> says she intends to
                keep a <sic>cosher</sic> house<lb/> herself when she goes to housekeeping<lb/> may
                be for <date>Pisach</date> she will, she is<lb/> getting over her <hi
                    rend="underline">religious</hi>
                <hi rend="underline">fit</hi> very<lb/> easily the force of example operates</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>3.</p>
            <p>greatly on some minds—x' tis<lb/> nearly ten and am expecting my<lb/> babe to wake
                and as I am her O...<lb/> nurse must prepare for her—<lb/>
                <persName>Malinaa</persName> is with me but poor thing<lb/> very
                    sickly—<persName>Miss Bridella</persName> is<lb/> also living with
                    us—<persName>Abraham</persName> has<lb/> gone with <persName>Joseph</persName>
                to keep store<lb/> in the country, we have <sic>too</sic> country<lb/> boys in place
                of him &amp; Father in<lb/> the store <sic>untill</sic>
                <persName>Mr Bloch</persName> can get<lb/> a good young man to attend to<lb/>
                business—adieu write by the<lb/> of <persName>Mr. Johnson</persName><lb/> return a
                    <hi rend="underline"><date>Pureem</date></hi>
                <hi rend="underline">Present</hi> a <hi rend="underline">Megilla</hi><lb/> I wish
                you a merry <date>Pureem</date></p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Your Friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">A B</persName> —</p>
            <p>Why did Poor <persName>Reinah</persName> leave Uncle's?<lb/> let me know all—</p>
            <p>Addressed to</p>
            <p>
                <hi rend="underline">Mr</hi>
                <addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>Polite attention<lb/> of<lb/>
                <persName>Mr Johnson</persName><lb/> W G P</p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p>
                <hi rend="underline">Mr</hi>
                <addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>Polite attention</p>
            <p>of</p>
            <p>
                <persName>Mr Johnson</persName>
            </p>
            <p>W G P</p>
        </body>
